window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>She’s scrappy and pure sunshine.</p> <p>He’s a 1,000-year-old vampire.</p> <p>Together they’re magic.</p> <p>Ever had life kick you in the teeth after it first stopped to shove you down the stairs?</p> <p>Yep. This used to be the story of my life.</p> <p>Until one day I saw an ad in the paper that changed everything—Wanted: Vampire’s Assistant. The list of qualifications that followed the listing for the job were ridiculous. Sturdiness? Not prone to fits of terror? Who posted stuff like this? Assuming it was a prank ad, I sent a very pointed email to the person who wrote it—Mr. Draven Leto…and immediately got a reply asking me to apply for the job.</p> <p>My scepticism didn’t last beyond a single phone call. I mean, someone taking over your body is something that’s difficult to refute. So now I’m on a plane heading for a place called Moonhaven Cove, somewhere off the coast of Oregon. A town hidden from humans. A town I get to enter because I’m not quite human myself.</p> <p>And my interview with Draven Leto, billionaire CEO of Leto Enterprises? Well, let’s just say it was life-changing.</p> <p>Wanted: Vampire’s Assistant is part of my new Moonhaven Cove series. The books in the series can be listened to on their own, but are more enjoyable if you listen to them in order. If you’re looking for clean paranormal romance with swoony kisses, snappy dialogue, funny and heartwarming characters, and plenty of suspense and action, you’ve found the right place.</p> <p>Welcome to Moonhaven Cove.</p>"; 
